@dermalogicacanada faves right now - ahem - perfect for Mother’s Day 💫
.
.
Dermalogica Dynamic Skin Retinol Serum.
3.5% retinoid complex + Squalane. 
-
🔷I use it 3x a week evenings obviously. If you have not used retinol before go slow ! This is perfect and you only need a tiny bit to see a big difference . @dermalogicacanada ‘s Squalane keeps your lipid barrier in check as the retinoids do their work .. 
.
This is the retinol serum I have reached for the most so far .. 
.
.
.
🔷Dermalogica Smart Response Serum . I use this every night before the dynamic retinol . It adjusts to your skins needs - and is a great base serum for my nighttime routine 💫
.
.
.
Lastly the newest from Dermalogica . Phyto Nature Oxygen cream - with hydrating oxygen optimizing phytoactives . Love love love . 
🔷
I use this as my last step- and wake up with skin that looks like it really got sleep ! Plumper skin - way more hydrated skin .. it’s like a mini oxygen facial every night.  I think their best product so far…
But they can do no wrong 💫
.
A+ @dermalogicacanada

 I must turn off comments for now 
My heart is in pieces and I must take care of my sons heart and mine 🙏🏻 

 

With love ❤️

Letter T 🐾around my neck forever ♾️ 
Standing in front of a light filled window 🪟- wet hair always makes me feel good .  mascara & cookies make me happy . And walks and seeing sunflowers 🌻. Carrying Tofu’s bag as a crossbody - purse 👛 makes me feel good . Blue 🩵 is my fave colour right now . Creating audio tracks for my teacher page on insight timer sends me to the clouds . Kinda where I live . My mom cut my hair - it’s shoulder length now - she said it looked too wild .. well .  Natural blonde yes . Haven’t touched it in years - hence - my mom … whatever hard stuff you’re going though right now . Do something beautiful with your emotions. Don’t keep them in . They will eventually come up like a volcano if you keep them in.  If you’re grieving - feel it .. accept those feelings and don’t run. Accept the kindness of strangers . For the ones that are big givers - please think of yourself first as your energy is different now.  Self care & the basics are the most important right now .. snuggle your stuffies. Listen to music you love . Remember emotions are like clouds . They change continuously . Best advice I can give as I’m waist deep in it -🌊. Is to reach out to people that - you know love you . Reach out to grief counsellors - Reach out to all your trusted sources.💫and know that you are never alone in the feelings you feel ..if you love big - you’re probably gonna grieve big . And there is no shame in that .. I’d rather have a huge heart … ♥️ 
be a gentle source of love for yourself … 🌊
